Bill,
I think I read somewhere that the decision to have the P-51B kit
without the dorsal fairing and the P-51C with the fairing was purely a
marketing decision. If you wanted a Razorback without the fillet, you
bought the P-51B kit, if you wanted it with the fillet you bought the
P-51C kit. No confusion (theoretically) would occur in the buyer's
mind as to what he was getting.
